2. Part09: PROVED closedFamilyChoice (+88 lines, was 736, now 824)
   - Replaced postulate with proof using LocalChoice + quotientBySeqPreservesBooleω
     + ImageStoneMapDecidableIntersection
   - Proof strategy:
     a. Apply LocalChoice to get C:Booleω, q:Sp C→→Sp B, and closed witnesses h
     b. Extract β : Sp C → ℕ → Bool, d' : ℕ → ⟨fst C⟩ via elemFromDecPred
     c. quotientBySeqPreservesBooleω on C and d' gives T:Booleω with
        Sp T ≃ {c : Sp C | ∀n. β(c,n)=false}
     d. Compose to get fT→B : Sp T → Sp B with Im(fT→B) = A
     e. ImageStoneMapDecidableIntersection gives d : ℕ → ⟨fst B⟩ with
        ∥Σ t. fT→B t ≡ x∥₁ ↔ ∀n. x(d n)=false
     f. Bidirectional proof: Im(fT→B)(x) ↔ A(transport SpB≡S x)
        - Forward: A(x) → surj gives c, h(c) gives β-false → t exists
        - Backward: t gives c in closed subset, h(c) backward gives A(x)
     g. Combine to get uniform α_y(n) = fst(transport(sym SpB≡S) y)(d n)
   - Added: open ODiscAxioms, import equivFun/invEq/secEq

